unity-reboot (0.2-1~webupd8~qr) quantal; urgency=medium
 
  * Update for new GRUB 2.0 stable menu list (with submenus) - only display the main menu entry
  * use pkexec for the grub-reboot command (but continue to use gksu for applying the settings - this way, if someone is using a DE that doesn't properly support pkexec can set Unity Reboot to reboot without entering a password (and thus, without pkexec)
  * some code cleaning
  * added postrm script to reset GRUB settings after removing unity-reboot
  * make desktop file executable or else it can't be dragged to the Ubuntu 13.04 launcher (maybe for 12.10 too?)
  * added gksu, bash as dependencies
 
 -- Alin Andrei <webupd8@gmail.com>  Tue, 22 Jan 2013 12:46:32 +0300

